EDIT:  As of December 13, I have uploaded a newer version with some minor fixes to the map.  I appologize to those of you who downloaded the older version, but because this was for a contest, I was forced to submit a map by the deadline.   Sorry again for this.  

And thank you to all of you who have left positive feedback so far!


This is a map I built for the Interlopers ZM Mapping Contest.  It is somewhat similar to zm_lila_panic, by Lila, so I have named it zm_panic for now.  It contains an open outdoor area, with a single chokepoint leading to an underground subway.  

This map was made in about two weeks, so its not as polished as I would have hoped, but it still turned out good I think.  The map plays best with a large number of people (24-32).  Enjoy!

zm_onadega_v3nn Map Features: Cubemaps Radar Map Extended Yard Custom Models More Accurate House New Camping Spots New Rooms Better Basement New Secret This is the third installment in the Onadega series of maps. For this one I went to the actual house with a laptop and set about making this version the most accurate version yet. Now the upstairs is much more realistic, the first floor is next to perfect, and even the basement approaches reality. There are still fake areas and the map isn't 100%, but I don't have a blueprint, so sue me. I also made a ton of custom map props such as mirrors so that the map would seem as real as possible. There are also many new textures and decals to add to the feel. I also extended the underground lab and added a new secret there. That's about it. If you like some of the stuff in the map such as custom props or texture, I have released a number of them already in the prefabs section, but if you want something you can't find, feel free to pakrat the map to get it out. As always, Questions & Comments are appreciated. - NatalyaAF -

zm_onadega_v2 Map Features: Cubemaps Radar Map A New Secret New Underground Area Better Looks This is a remake of zm_onadega, as you might guess. This version is mostly scenery changes, but I also added an underground lab area and extended the area around the house for you to play on, though it's still mostly field. I also added 1 new secret, and made the house look more like the actual house. I also added a TV antenna tower that they have at the back. You can climb it as a ladder to get to the roof. All old secrets stayed the same except the hard one under the deck. I also re-did all the terrain around the house, so it looks sexy. *EDIT* The map has now been up to _v2a with 5 minor bug fixes. Questions & Comments are appreciated.

zm_onadega Map Features: - 48 Player Spawns - Cubemaps - Radar Map - 4 Easy Secrets - 2 Medium Secrets - Barricading Spots - Climbing Spots Okay, this map is probably the smallest I've released. It's a 2-story house with a basement, garage, and tiny play house. The map is based off of my cousin's house in Onadega, Ontario. The first floor is almost 100% accurate, but the second floor has some rooms merged, and the basement is completely original, except the staircase and door to the outside. The house also has too many windows. O well, it's a game right? Anyway, the map does have a bunch of secrets like all my maps. Some are easy, a couple are hard. (Invisible buttons & stuff...) This map was made small so that when there are only a few people on a server, it doesn't take forever to find them, but when there are a lot there is a decent spot for everyone. Thanks to MoOnLiGht for testing this map on the Zombie Network II server: 81.95.0.26:27035 (Unlimited Ammo, No Reload, Prop Menu) All custom materials are paked into the map, including the radar. Let me know if you have texture missing bugs, but I don't think there will be any. Tell me what you guys think!! PS: Minor note regarding the flag and symbols on the house: My extended family is Latvian, and that's the flag of Latvia. The wooden symbol is something they'll put on their houses, but I don't know what it means or signifies, just that my cousins have one on their house, so I put it up too.

Hey Guys,

Thank you for taking an interest in my map. I have been out of the mapping scene since the early days of TFC, so I am very excited about this release. It is the first version so any bug or glitches found I would be happy to hear about. 

I have to thank all the guys over at {BHF} as well, they where all such a huge help in making this.

Hope everyone enjoys it!

Overview:

This is an Aztec themed map, in which the premise is to use "jump pads" scattered throughout the level to access the "camping points". There are a few hidden secretes and traps as well. The map relies on shooting accuracy and team work, no barricades here, so don't expect to live long solo. This is a very large map so make sure it is played with at least 18 people.  

=========================
*V2
1.Fixed spawning issue where players would get stuck to each other
2.Added arrow textures to jump pads to show the correct launch direction
3.Shortened beginning to allow more time for players to set up throughout the level
4.fixed some random textures
=========================

Hey Guys,

So after getting a lot of feedback on my Olin map, I decided to make a spin off of it. I took everyones complaints, suggestions, and compliments and blended it into what I hope is a better map over all. This map contains many of the aspects Olin had but is blended into something a bit more seamless. As always feedback is very much appreciated.

Note* this being the beta version there is no lighting, I plan on adding it in version one of the map after I see how this one plays out.

Credits:
•BHF as always for helping me test this out
•BarneyBoy's Letgo Texture Pack (http://berneyboy.planetquake.gamespy.com/letgo_info.htm) for making an awesome set of textures and saving me loads of time for not having to do em myself ;)

Hope everyone enjoys this!

=========================================================
V1 Changes:

•Fine tuned the jump pads for smoother game play
•Increased speed in Hovering Platforms.
•Added some hidden brushes to prevent players from falling to their deaths.
•Blocks removed at top of temple, added ramps to speed up game play
•Other fixes too small to name. 
=========================================================
V2 Changes:

•Added button to spin pink wire around to prevent excessive camping
•Other various tweaks to enhance game play for both sides.
=========================================================
V3 Changes:

•Drastically dumbed down jump pads and added many preventions to players 
flying  to their deaths.
•Sped up game play and added further balancing changes.
•Added 64 spawn points.
•Fixed some texture issues.
•A few other minor tweaks

*Just a note, this map should play out much smoother now, I have spent a lot of work on the frustrating aspects and balanced out the team play best as possible. Any feedback would be greatly appreciated before I release the final version.
=========================================================

This is my second zm map, this is based on an idustrial type enviroment.
The map contains many places for camping, there is a varied amount of spots, there is on rooftops, on containers, on vans, inside rooms, on cars 
and on trains .

When you spawn you will be in a room, you go down the stairs and go onto one of the platforms in the room, this will then teleport you to a location, there are 5  teleports, 10 in total (5 T teleport and 5 CT teleports) the Terrerist and the CT's get teleport to different ends of the map, you dont have to use your teams teleports, their is a corridor connecting the two spawns, so you could go use the Terrorist teleport. I decided to use the teleport idea because i thought it will help cut down the ammount of spawn camping that goes on in Zombie Mod, people will proberly say " Then they will just camp at the teleport exits" the teleport exits are in open space so if a zombie is camping there he will be getting blown to bits by people on roofs, on cars, vans and peopel inside rooms, so the zombies will not be able to just stand there and camp they will be forced to move.

There are in total 26 CT spawns and 26 t spawns, i put this many in so different servers can use it. When i tested it i got a fine FPS in the hundreds.

Please leave some feedback if you download this map.

This is my first complete map using hammer editor, still learning new things all the time.
I wanted a zm map which had no vents or stupidly impossiable places for the zombies to reach and this is what I have came up with!

Bottom floor of the map is pretty much all rooms with the normal barricade props like the bookcase, sofa and vending machines, bottom floor gives a safe place for zombie to hide if his the only zombie with 49 cts looking for him, some nice places for the zombie to make a counter attack.

Top floor of the map is outside, bright and green, hardly any barricade props and not very surcure for lone cts, if you work as a team then you should see a few zombies dropping.
Top floor was mainly designed for hunting.

I think the design of the map will make for fast, fun and funny gameplay  without people being able to sit in a vent all day with an M3 shotgun!
